message.content:
A Corvus splendens is a bird commonly known as the house crow.
It has a shiny black plumage.
The bill and legs are also black.
The eyes are small and set forward in the head.
The wingspan averages around 90 cm.
It is commonly found in urban, suburban, and coastal areas of India and surrounding countries.
It is an opportunistic feeder, consuming a variety of foods including insects, small animals, and human garbage.
